Task 2 – Multi-Threading / Fundamentals

Q1: You downloaded an instruction booklet on how to make an origami crane. What would this instruction booklet resemble in computer terms?
→ Program

Q2: What is the name of the state where a process is waiting for an I/O event?
→ Waiting

Task 3 – Race Conditions (concept questions)

Q1: Does the presented Python script guarantee which thread will reach 100 % first? (Yea/Nay)
→ Nay

Q2: In the second execution of the Python script, what is the name of the thread that reached 100 % first?
→ Thread-1

Task 4 – Web Application States

Q1: How many states did the original state diagram of “validating and conducting money transfer” have?
→ 2 (Amount not sent, Amount sent)

Q2: How many states did the updated state diagram of “validating and conducting money transfer” have?
→ 3 (Amount not sent, Checking balance and account limits, Amount sent)

Q3: How many states did the final state diagram of “validating coupon codes and applying discounts” have?
→ 5 (Coupon not applied, Checking coupon validity, Checking coupon constraints, Recalculating total, Coupon applied)

Task 5 – Exploiting Race Conditions

Q: You need to get either of the accounts to get more than $100 of credit to get the flag. What is the flag that you obtained?
→ THM{PHONE-RACE}

